Last night I was able to help do makeup at Night to Shine hosted at our church, One Life. Being able to help make some of the most precious people I’ve ever met feel beautiful is a feeling I can’t even begin to describe. Gods presence was so powerful and I left last night overwhelmed feeling his love for us. 

Some days I fall short, I fail and I’m far from perfect but we belong to a God who gives us mercy and grace even on our worst days. Thank you God for showing me I am worthy of your love. Thank you for this church family and thank you for the opportunity to serve you and our community. I can’t wait to continue to grow and be better through you. 

Always remember, Jesus loves you ❤️
#nightoshine #nighttoshine2023 @onelifechurch @timtebow

At this point I don’t even know how long you’ve been my Valentine, but I’m glad it’s been for as long as I can remember. 

You’re my best friend, the keeper of my heart, the one guiding me to be more like Jesus, the man I wake up in the middle of the night when I can’t breathe right, my lover, my baby daddy, the sexiest coach on the court, my playlist maker, the one who tells me to stop with all the target trips and all the things in between. 

You have shown me to live life to the fullest and to try and not be scared. You are my forever Valentine. 

I love you @hl_hartt thank you for being MINE.
